excerpt: Upscale shopping district lined with boutiques, restaurants & numerous art galleries.
detail_description: E Las Olas Blvd is an upscale shopping district in Downtown Fort Lauderdale, featuring boutiques, restaurants, and art galleries. The area is also home to the sleek boutique beauty Hyatt Centric Las Olas, offering guests a prime location near the boulevard, Riverwalk, and cultural institutions. Some rooms provide stunning city views and overlook the New River where yachts parade by.
name: E Las Olas Blvd
address: Fort Lauderdale, FL, USA

excerpt: Verdant, storied, 1920s-era plantation home featuring gardens, an arty interior, tours & more.
detail_description: Bonnet House Museum & Gardens is a historic 1920s plantation home in Fort Lauderdale, once owned by American artists Frederic and Evelyn Barlett. The estate features an art gallery, lush gardens, and environmental preservation on its 35-acre property. It offers a glimpse of Old Florida architecture, with Frederic's murals adorning the ceilings and Evelyn's unique collection of monkey art.
name: Bonnet House Museum & Gardens
address: 900 N Birch Rd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

excerpt: Downtown facility offering interactive exhibits for kids & adults, eco-center & giant IMAX theater.
detail_description: The Museum of Discovery and Science, situated in the heart of Fort Lauderdale's arts and science district, is a popular destination for both kids and adults. Established in 1977, this downtown facility spans 150,000 square feet and features interactive exhibits, an eco-center, a giant IMAX theater, an outdoor science park, live animal displays, and engaging science demonstrations.
name: Museum of Discovery and Science
address: 401 SW 2nd St, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33312, USA

excerpt: Featuring a freshwater lagoon, this diverse wildlife habitat offers hiking, fishing & more.
detail_description: Hugh Taylor Birch State Park in Fort Lauderdale is a testament to the city's history and natural beauty. Originally acquired by Hugh Taylor Birch in 1893 as a retreat, the park remained largely undeveloped until 1940 when Birch began construction on his residence. The park features a diverse wildlife habitat with marsh rabbits, turtles, and gopher tortoises among its inhabitants. Visitors can enjoy activities such as hiking, fishing, and exploring the freshwater lagoon.
name: Hugh Taylor Birch State Park
address: 3109 E Sunrise Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

excerpt: Complex with more than 6,000 works of art, plus an academy, bookstore & cafe.
detail_description: NSU Art Museum Fort Lauderdale is a cultural hub in Broward County, boasting an extensive collection of over 7,500 works from renowned artists worldwide. The museum features post-war and Latin-American art, offering visitors unique insights into these influential movements.
name: NSU Art Museum Fort Lauderdale
address: 1 E Las Olas Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: 7+ miles of sandy oceanfront featuring water sports & a promenade plus access to shopping & dining.
detail_description: Fort Lauderdale Beach spans over 7 miles of sandy oceanfront, offering a variety of water sports and a lively promenade with access to shopping and dining. The city is known as the yachting capital of the U.S., making it almost essential to explore its waterways by boat. Visitors can opt for a local water taxi with multiple stops or enjoy a private experience on an electric gondola tour or boat charter.
name: Fort Lauderdale Beach
address: Jimmy Buffett Mem Hwy, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

excerpt: Guided visit around a 1901 trading post later converted to a local businessman's family residence.
detail_description: Historic Stranahan House Museum, dating back to 1901, is the oldest surviving building in the county and has witnessed over a century of Fort Lauderdale's rich history. Originally a trading post, it was later transformed into the residence of the Stranahan family in 1906. The family played a significant role in shaping the city's early development and holds a revered place in its collective memory as pioneers.
name: Historic Stranahan House Museum
address: 335 SE 6th Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Fort Lauderdale is a city on Florida's southeastern coast, known for its beaches and boating canals. The Strip is a promenade running along oceanside highway A1A. It's lined with upscale outdoor restaurants, bars, boutiques and luxury hotels. Other attractions include the International Swimming Hall of Fame, with pools and a museum of memorabilia, and Hugh Taylor Birch State Park, featuring trails and a lagoon.
detail_description: Fort Lauderdale, situated on Florida's southeastern coast, is renowned for its stunning beaches and intricate boating canals. The city boasts the Strip, a vibrant promenade along A1A highway with upscale dining spots, bars, boutiques, and luxury hotels. Visitors can explore attractions like the International Swimming Hall of Fame and Hugh Taylor Birch State Park. Inland from the beach lies Downtown Fort Lauderdale on the New River banks.
name: Fort Lauderdale
address: Florida, USA

detail_description: Situated in downtown Fort Lauderdale, the Broward Center for the Performing Arts offers a wide array of entertainment and educational experiences to the community. Overlooking the New River, this renowned venue hosts over 700 concerts, shows, and performances annually, attracting more than 600,000 patrons. From Broadway musicals to ballets, operas to plays, and concerts to multi-cultural events, there's something for everyone.
name: Broward center
address: E Broward Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Charming park on the banks of the New River with a wide array of galleries, museums & eateries.
detail_description: Riverwalk Fort Lauderdale is a charming park located along the banks of the New River, offering a variety of galleries, museums, and eateries. It is a nonprofit organization that has partnered with local groups to create an intentional destination for both locals and visitors. The park features beautifully landscaped areas where visitors can take leisurely strolls, enjoy delicious food from nearby eateries, and catch live shows.
name: Riverwalk Fort Lauderdale
address: 888 E Las Olas Blvd #210, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Vintage riverboat offering sightseeing tours of Fort Lauderdale waterways, dinner & show cruises.
detail_description: The Jungle Queen Riverboat is a vintage riverboat that provides sightseeing tours and dinner cruises along the New River and the Intracoastal Waterway in Fort Lauderdale. The captain narrates interesting stories about the city's history, pointing out opulent mansions of celebrities, rock stars, and corporate elite along Millionaires Row.
name: Jungle Queen Riverboat
address: 801 Seabreeze Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33316, USA

excerpt: Interactive cruise where passengers learn buccaneer talk, search for treasure & help fire cannons.
detail_description: BlueFoot Pirate Adventures in Fort Lauderdale offers an interactive cruise where passengers can immerse themselves in the world of buccaneers. Families can join this 90-minute trip, starting with a message in a bottle and embarking on a quest to find hidden treasure. The adventure includes facing off against Barnacle Bill in a water battle aboard an enemy ship. At the end of the journey, junior pirates receive a bag of booty for their brave service. This experience takes place along Ft.
name: BlueFoot Pirate Adventures
address: Dock G28, 151 N Beach Rd, Dania Beach, FL 33004, USA

excerpt: Museum featuring motor cars & memorabilia, plus a gallery dedicated to Franklin Delano Roosevelt.
detail_description: If you're a fan of classic cars and rich history, the Fort Lauderdale Antique Car Museum is an absolute must-visit. This remarkable establishment serves as a non-profit foundation dedicated to educating visitors about the illustrious Packard Motor Company and American engineering advancements. Inside its expansive 30,000 square-foot space, you'll find an impressive collection of over 22 meticulously maintained Packard automobiles from the early 1900s to the 1940s, each showcasing unique features like specialized golf club compartments.
name: The Fort Lauderdale Antique Car Museum
address: 1527 SW 1st Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33315, USA

detail_description: The historic Fort Lauderdale Fire Station has been converted into a museum dedicated to the history of fire safety. The exhibits include antique fire engines and equipment, uniforms from the 1920s, and a special children's area where young visitors can get their hands on some of the equipment.
name: Fort Lauderdale Fire and Safety Museum, Inc.
address: 1022 W Las Olas Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33312, USA

excerpt: Museum honoring swimmers & divers, with aquatic memorabilia such as Olympic medals on display.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant city of Fort Lauderdale, Florida, the International Swimming Hall of Fame is a must-visit for aquatic enthusiasts and history buffs alike. This remarkable museum celebrates the achievements of swimmers and divers from around the globe, showcasing an impressive collection of memorabilia including Olympic medals that tell stories of triumph and dedication. Established in 1965 and renovated in 1991, this complex features not only a fascinating museum but also a world-class aquatic center where visitors can immerse themselves in all things swimming.
name: International Swimming Hall of Fame Giftshop
address: 1 Hall of Fame Dr, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33316, USA

excerpt: This busy public beach offers white sand & palm trees, plus restaurants, lodging & stores.
detail_description: Las Olas Beach is a bustling public beach with white sand, palm trees, and various amenities such as restaurants, lodging, and stores. It's located in East Fort Lauderdale near attractions like Bonnet House Museum and Gardens. The area offers pristine beaches and vibrant nightlife on Las Olas Boulevard. Visitors can also explore the charming neighborhood of Wilton Manors nearby. The beach provides a perfect setting for relaxation with its beautiful coastal scenery, inviting waters, and numerous spots to unwind.
name: Las Olas Beach
address: 240 Las Olas Cir, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

excerpt: Small, historic museum packed with displays about naval aviation, World War II history & Flight 19.
detail_description: The Naval Air Station Fort Lauderdale Museum preserves history and honors the heroes of WWII. The museum is packed with displays about naval aviation, World War II history and Flight 19.
name: Naval Air Station Fort Lauderdale Museum
address: 4000 W Perimeter Rd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33315, USA

excerpt: Family-friendly park with swimming, fishing, boating & diving. Home to wild birds & sea turtles.
detail_description: Dr. Von D. Mizell-Eula Johnson State Park, situated in Dania Beach, Florida, is a historic coastal retreat with deep roots in the civil rights history of South Florida. It offers a family-friendly environment with activities such as swimming, fishing, boating, and diving. The park is home to various wildlife including wild birds and sea turtles.
name: Dr. Von D. Mizell-Eula Johnson State Park
address: 6503 N Ocean Dr, Dania Beach, FL 33004, USA

excerpt: Broward County's oldest standing hotel, preserved as a history museum with prints, books & artworks.
detail_description: History Fort Lauderdale, Broward County's oldest standing hotel, has been transformed into a history museum that houses prints, books, and artworks. The institution is dedicated to collecting and preserving materials from the community's past to help present and future generations understand their predecessors and themselves. It offers public lectures, workshops, teacher resources, group tours, research assistance, and maintains historic structures dating back to 1905.
name: History Fort Lauderdale
address: 231 SW 2nd Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Complex with a half-mile asphalt go-kart track, bowling lanes, an indoor ropes course & a bar.
detail_description: Xtreme Action Park is a massive 200,000 square foot indoor entertainment venue in Florida, offering a wide range of thrilling activities for visitors of all ages. From go-kart racing on a half-mile track to bowling, arcade games, ropes course adventure, trampoline park, roller skating rink, escape rooms, laser tag and virtual reality games - there's something for everyone.
name: Xtreme Action Park
address: 5300 Powerline Rd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33309, USA

excerpt: Options abound at this Italian stunner with Neapolitan pies, pastas, salumi & a piazza with bocce.
detail_description: Louie Bossi's Ristorante Bar Pizzeria is a bustling Italian restaurant located on Fort Lauderdale's Las Olas Boulevard. The interior boasts charming features like tin ceilings, rustic wood beams, and tufted leather booths, while the outdoor courtyard offers a garden-like setting with brick pathways, fire pits, and even a bocce court.
name: Louie Bossi's Ristorante Bar Pizzeria
address: 1032 E Las Olas Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Famous oceanfront area providing a range of water & beach activities, lifeguards & scenic views.
detail_description: Fort Lauderdale Beaches, stretching over twenty miles of golden sands, offer a wide range of water and beach activities, lifeguard services, and stunning views of the Atlantic Ocean. The beachfront promenade is lined with shops, restaurants, and entertainment options for visitors to enjoy. Fort Lauderdale Beach provides more than 50 activities to indulge in and nearly 70 dining options. From watersports to spas, shops to nightlife venues, there's something for everyone.
name: Fort Lauderdale Beaches
address: 1686 N Fort Lauderdale Beach Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33305, USA

detail_description: Invasive Species Brewing, founded in 2017 by a talented team including Phil Gillis and Josh Levitt, is quickly becoming a beloved destination for beer enthusiasts in Fort Lauderdale. This unique brewpub operates on a five-barrel system and showcases an impressive rotation of 10 craft beers that often incorporate local Florida ingredients. Signature brews like the Bleubird Saison, aged with hand-picked blueberries, and the PassionBerry Sour highlight their commitment to innovation.
name: Invasive Species Brewing + Distilling
address: 726 NE 2nd Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

excerpt: Chill, beachy hangout on the Intracoastal dishing seafood & Sunday brunch while yachts cruise by.
detail_description: Nestled along the Intracoastal Waterway, Coconuts is a top choice for dining in Fort Lauderdale. This restaurant offers an upscale yet casual experience with stunning views of the waterways, making it perfect for watching boats and enjoying beautiful sunsets. Known for its delectable seafood dishes like coconut shrimp and jambalaya, Coconuts also features daily specials such as scallops.
name: Coconuts
address: 429 Seabreeze Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Festive local landmark serving up Chinese fare, tropical drinks & a Polynesian floor show.
detail_description: Mai-Kai Restaurant and Polynesian Show is a vibrant local landmark that has been drawing in crowds since 1956. The restaurant offers a lively atmosphere with tiki bars, traditional Polynesian performances, and colorful South Seas cuisine. Guests can enjoy exotic dishes and tropical drinks from an award-winning menu while being entertained by agile warriors and beautiful maidens performing native dances from the South Pacific.
name: MAI-KAI Restaurant and Polynesian Show
address: 3599 N Federal Hwy, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33308, USA

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of downtown Fort Lauderdale's Flagler Village, Circle House Coffee is a vibrant community coffee shop that has been serving top-notch coffee since its establishment in 2018 by Stephen Tulloch, a former NFL player. The cafe offers a variety of experiences including quick grab-and-go service at the drive-thru, as well as indoor and outdoor patio seating.
name: Circle House Coffee
address: 727 NE 3rd Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

detail_description: MASS District, situated in Fort Lauderdale's Progresso Village neighborhood, is a vibrant hub for creativity and art. The area boasts colorful street art murals, along with an array of restaurants, art studios, and small businesses. Visitors can enjoy the monthly Fort Lauderdale ArtWalk and the Sunny Side Up Market featuring over 90 vendors and artists. Additionally, Sistrunk Marketplace & Brewery in Progresso Village showcases captivating murals by renowned artists.
name: MASS District
address: 844 NE 4th Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

detail_description: Fort Lauderdale Beach Park's Playground is a scenic park located on Seabreeze Boulevard, offering various amenities and activities for visitors. It features picnic areas with tables and grills, clean restrooms, outdoor showers, basketball and volleyball courts, and a boating ramp for non-motorized boats. The park is less crowded than other nearby beaches, making it popular among families. With its picturesque ocean views and abundant facilities, Fort Lauderdale Beach Park provides an ideal setting for a day of outdoor fun.
name: Fort Lauderdale Beach Park's Playground
address: 1005 Seabreeze Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33316, USA

excerpt: Polished rooms & suites in a posh beachfront hotel offering a spa, 2 outdoor pools & dining.
detail_description: Situated on the beautiful Fort Lauderdale Beach, Four Seasons Hotel and Residences Fort Lauderdale offers luxurious beachfront accommodations with a range of amenities. The hotel features polished rooms and suites, two outdoor pools, a spa offering waterway-inspired treatments, and dining options including an Eastern Mediterranean/coastal-influenced menu at Evelyns Table. Guests can also enjoy free WiFi throughout the property and access to facilities such as a kids' club and an ATM.
name: Four Seasons Hotel And Residences Fort Lauderdale
address: 525 N Fort Lauderdale Beach Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

detail_description: The Katherine Restaurant, located in Fort Lauderdale, is a popular spot known for its diverse and globally-inspired menu. The restaurant recently introduced a Sunday brunch featuring unique dishes like Thai red curry shrimp and grits, truffle beet toast, and carbonara mac. Accompany your meal with refreshing cocktails such as mimosas or jalapeno bloody Mary, or choose from a selection of local beers and natural wines.
name: The Katherine Restaurant
address: 723 E Broward Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

detail_description: Fort Lauderdale International Boat Show (FLIBS) is a major event that takes place in October, attracting a large number of boats and yachts to the Hall of Fame Marina and the Bahia Mar yachting center. The show features exhibitions and displays of various types of boats, making it a great opportunity to see a wide variety of vessels.
name: Fort Lauderdale International Boat Show (FLIBS)
address: 801 Seabreeze Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33316, USA

detail_description: The Sun Trolley in Fort Lauderdale is a convenient and affordable way to explore the city. With seven routes covering various areas including the beach, neighborhoods, downtown, and even connecting to the airport bus, it offers both price and convenience. The trolley has been an integral part of the city since 1992 and continues to provide locals and tourists with an easy way to get around town. Recent improvements have made it better than ever.
name: Sun Trolley
address: 290 NE 3rd Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Sophisticated 2-story shopping mall offers fashionable retail stores & eateries, plus valet parking.
detail_description: Nestled conveniently near the beach on Sunrise Boulevard, The Galleria at Fort Lauderdale is a sophisticated two-story shopping destination that perfectly embodies the city's upscale vibe. This vibrant mall features over 100 retail stores and dining options, making it one of South Florida's premier shopping spots and the largest in Broward County. Shoppers can explore renowned anchor stores like Neiman Marcus, Dillard's, and Macy's alongside trendy boutiques such as Coach and Banana Republic.
name: The Galleria at Fort Lauderdale
address: 2414 E Sunrise Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

excerpt: Warehouse district with a monthly art walk featuring open galleries, artisan goods, food & music.
detail_description: FATVillage Arts District, also known as Flagler Arts and Technology Village, is an emerging warehouse district in Fort Lauderdale. It hosts a monthly art walk featuring open galleries, artisan goods, food, and music. This 5.6-acre district is akin to Miami's Wynwood with its converted warehouses housing contemporary art galleries and co-working spaces like General Provision. The area showcases unique creations from local artisans including handmade jewelry, original artwork, and one-of-a-kind fashion pieces.
name: FATVillage Arts District
address: 521 NW 1st Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Easygoing specialty beer boutique & kitchen serving an eclectic menu amid couches & beachy decor.
detail_description: The Riverside Market Cafe is a laid-back spot that offers a diverse menu and an extensive selection of over 550 craft beers, specialty wines, gourmet sodas, teas, and waters. The eclectic decor includes mixed-matched couches for visitors to relax and enjoy their drinks. It's popular among both beer enthusiasts and newcomers to the craft beer scene. Additionally, it's known for its authentic Jewish deli experience and standout breakfast sandwiches.
name: The Riverside Market Cafe
address: 608 SW 12th Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33312, USA

excerpt: Small park & green space on the water popular for picnics, river fishing & scenic views.
detail_description: Colee Hammock Park is a serene and picturesque green space located by the water, offering a peaceful retreat from the bustling city. It's an ideal spot for picnics, leisurely walks, and river fishing. The park's lush greenery and scenic views make it a perfect place to relax and unwind. Visitors can enjoy watching boats pass by on the river or simply find a quiet corner to read a book or hang a hammock.
name: Colee Hammock Park
address: 1500 Brickell Dr, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

detail_description: New River Fine Art is a world-renowned art gallery that focuses on showcasing the latest and greatest works by famous artists. The gallery features a variety of styles, including Impressionist, 20th century, post-war and contemporary paintings. They also feature pieces by local artists, such as Tom Rossetti and Joshua Tiktin. Monthly exhibitions are held with special guest speakers and always attract a large crowd.
name: New River Fine Art
address: 822 E Las Olas Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Urban wilderness area including butterfly garden, reptile habitat & nature trails on 57 acres.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of South Florida, Secret Woods Nature Center is a hidden oasis spanning 57 acres. This urban wilderness area boasts a butterfly garden, reptile habitat, and nature trails that wind through dense mangrove forests. Visitors can enjoy educational programs, interactive exhibits, and a serene atmosphere while reconnecting with nature. The center offers a tranquil retreat from city life and provides opportunities to observe indigenous wildlife in their natural habitat.
name: Secret Woods Nature Center
address: 2701 W State Rd 84, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33312, USA

excerpt: Upscale eatery serving locally sourced New American and coastal cuisine, along with sushi and drinks.
detail_description: S3, short for Sun, Surf, and Sand, is an upscale eatery located in Fort Lauderdale offering a chic dining experience with a menu featuring locally sourced New American and coastal cuisine, sushi, and drinks. The restaurant's beachfront location provides stunning views of the Atlantic Ocean and its stylish decor makes it a popular spot for both locals and visitors.
name: S3 (Sun Surf Sand)
address: 505 N Fort Lauderdale Beach Blvd Suite S, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

excerpt: Stylish surf shop selling paddleboards & gear as well as offering board rentals & guided tours.
detail_description: Sunrise Paddleboards, LLC. is a stylish surf shop that not only sells paddleboards and gear but also offers board rentals and guided tours. The staff is known for being excellent and knowledgeable, providing assistance in learning to paddle or purchasing a board. They are also happy to take photos of visitors enjoying their time on the water. Customers have praised the staff's friendliness and helpfulness, particularly when it comes to organizing events such as birthday parties for kids.
name: Sunrise PaddleBoards
address: 2520 N Federal Hwy, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33305, USA

detail_description: Cruisin' Tikis Fort Lauderdale offers a delightful boat ride along the Fort Lauderdale waterways, providing a refreshing and scenic experience. Whether you opt for a morning or afternoon cruise, or enjoy the sunset views on an evening excursion, this floating bar promises a fun-filled time. With a maximum capacity of six people, it's perfect for small groups looking to relax and take in the beautiful shoreline scenery.
name: Cruisin' Tikis Fort Lauderdale
address: 501 S New River Dr E, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Long-running beach bar with live bands & DJ dancing, luring perennial spring-breakers.
detail_description: Located at the bustling intersection of Las Olas Boulevard and A1A, Elbo Room has been a popular beach bar since 1938. It gained fame in the 1960s with the movie 'Where The Boys Are' and has been a go-to spot for generations of spring breakers. With live music, ocean views, and a vibrant atmosphere, it continues to attract tourists and locals alike.
name: Elbo Room
address: 241 S Fort Lauderdale Beach Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33316, USA

excerpt: A collegiate crowd frequents this spacious & festive bar with DJ dancing & occasional live bands.
detail_description: Backyard is a popular spot in downtown Fort Lauderdale, known for its spacious and lively atmosphere. It's a favorite among the collegiate crowd, offering a large outdoor party space with room to dance and enjoy live music. The venue features an eclectic and relaxed ambiance, perfect for unwinding after a day of exploring the area. With its beer garden just steps away from the Museum of Discovery and Science, visitors can savor homemade pizza and signature craft brews while listening to live DJ mixes.
name: Backyard
address: 100 SW 3rd Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33312, USA

excerpt: Roomy destination with a convivial vibe featuring global food outlets, plus craft ales.
detail_description: Sistrunk Marketplace & Brewery is a spacious and lively destination that offers a diverse range of global food options and craft ales. This 40,000-square-foot indoor foodie village in Flagler Village goes beyond being just a food hall, featuring an island bar, speakeasy-style lounge, retail shopping co-op, DJ academy, recording studio, and ample seating. Reservations are available but not required, and guests can conveniently order from multiple food stalls using a QR code from their phones.
name: Sistrunk Marketplace & Brewery
address: 115 NW 6th St, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33311, USA

excerpt: Laid-back hangout with old-school arcade games & pinball, weekend DJs, trivia nights & a full bar.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Flagler Village of Fort Lauderdale, Glitch Bar is a delightful fusion of nostalgia and modern fun. This laid-back hangout invites you to relive your childhood with an impressive array of old-school arcade games and pinball machines, all while enjoying a craft beer or one of their creative cocktails like the "Player 1: Old Fashioned." The atmosphere buzzes with energy from weekend DJs and trivia nights, making it a perfect spot for socializing.
name: Glitch Bar
address: 905 NE 5th Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA

detail_description: Las Olas Oceanside Park, part of The LOOP in Fort Lauderdale, offers more than just a beach experience. It's one of four green spaces that make up The LOOP and is where much of the action happens. This park hosts events like the Memorial Day bash with live music, car shows, and food vendors. Visitors can also enjoy shopping on Las Olas Boulevard or relax in the park's shaded areas with palm trees and a constant breeze.
name: Las Olas Oceanside Park
address: 3000 E Las Olas Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33316, USA

detail_description: The Bellagio International Gallery is an art gallery that sells high-quality pieces of art. The staff is extremely helpful, and they will work with you to find the right piece of art for your home. In addition, the gallery offers a wide range of services, such as framing and shipping. If you're in Vegas and are looking for some high-quality art, be sure to check out the Bellagio International Gallery!
name: Bellagio International Gallery
address: 806 E Las Olas Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33301, USA

excerpt: Sprawling 1960s facility with a flea market, a Ferrari museum & a 14-screen drive-in movie theater.
detail_description: Fort Lauderdale Swap Shop is a must-visit, known as the South's largest flea market. The vibrant yellow people bridge over Sunrise Boulevard invites visitors to explore this unique experience. It offers a diverse range of items from clothing and household goods to fresh produce. The food court features various vendors, including Las Reinas with live music and Mexican cuisine. For Latino visitors, it feels like a familiar mercadito filled with fresh fruits and friendly competition among vendors.
name: Fort Lauderdale Swap Shop
address: 3291 W Sunrise Blvd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33311, USA

excerpt: Bustling, contemporary kitchen offering specialty pizzas & colorful salads, plus beer & cocktails.
detail_description: Heritage is a vibrant and modern restaurant located in the arts district of Fort Lauderdale. The chef/owner, Rino Cerbone, has redefined Italian cuisine with a focus on quality and innovation. The menu offers a variety of specialty pizzas, colorful salads, and small plates such as squash blossoms and agrodocle calamari. The intimate setting makes it advisable to make reservations in advance. This popular spot has become a favorite for celebrations and enjoyable evenings out.
name: Heritage
address: 903 NE 5th Ave, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304, USA
